casebody.data:
Office of Disciplinary Counsel v. Doyle.

[Cite as Disciplinary Counsel v. Doyle (1995), 71 Ohio St.3d 574.]

(No. 94-1839 Submitted January 10, 1995 Decided March 1, 1995.) *575Geoffrey Stem, Disciplinary Counsel, and Sally Ann Steuk, Assistant Disciplinary Counsel, for relator. Per Curiam.

Having reviewed the record, we concur in the board’s findings and its recommendation. Accordingly, we order that respondent be indefinitely suspended from the practice of law in Ohio. Costs taxed to respondent.

Judgment accordingly.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Wright, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer and Cook, JJ., concur.
